From a2183cb3f6ab33bfa23c7a85f652c7260f216bcb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kapilash <kapilash@example.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 15:19:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add retrieval-quality evaluation harness (Phase 1 baseline
 metrics)

Implements the remaining piece of the roadmap's Phase 1 milestone:
'Add evaluation questions and baseline quality metrics.'

- mars_ai_os.knowledge.evaluation: EvaluationCase (labeled question ->
  expected source document(s)), EvaluationOutcome (hit@1, hit@3,
  reciprocal rank per case), EvaluationReport (aggregate hit_rate_at_1,
  hit_rate_at_3, mean_reciprocal_rank, failing_cases()), run_evaluation()
- KnowledgeService.retrieve(): exposes raw ranked passages (ask() now
  built on top of it) so evaluation can score retrieval without
  requiring an Answerer
- Expanded the bundled sample corpus 2 -> 5 documents (atmosphere,
  gravity, moons, geology, rovers) and added 7 labeled evaluation
  questions in knowledge/demo.py
- New CLI command: mars-ai-os knowledge-eval
- Measured baseline for the default HashingEmbedder, recorded in
  docs/KNOWLEDGE_ENGINE.md and enforced as a regression floor:
  hit_rate_at_1 ~0.71, hit_rate_at_3 = 1.0, MRR ~0.86. Two questions
  rank a longer, topically-varied document above the exact match -
  documented honestly as the concrete gap a real embedding model
  should close, not hidden behind an idealized 1.0 assertion
- 7 new tests (full suite: 51 passed), ruff check clean
